This is empanaderia is always bumpin'.  15-20 selections of savory empanadas, plus sweet empanadas and other desserts, and tasty-looking salads.  This place has got some indoor seating, and plenty of outdoor seating.  I got a clara, and a selection of empanadas.  The service was great--the woman serving up the empanadas was really patient with my Spanish, even though it was really busy, and she even translated a few of the unknowns into English for me.  After I selected what I wanted, they were put into an oven, and brought to a perfectly palatable temperature.  The eggplant & cheese, the tuna, the caprese, and the Roquefort with walnuts are all excellent.
